## Code conventions
- TypeScript strict, no `any`
- File names: kebab-case
- Conventional Commits (`feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`)
- Errors: typed errors, no silent catch

## WHAT NOT TO DO ⛔
<!-- THE most important section. After every Claude mistake, append the lesson here. -->
- DO NOT use `npm install` — only `pnpm`
- DO NOT create barrel files (`index.ts` re-export aggregators)
- DO NOT mock the database in tests — we use testcontainers
- DO NOT commit without going through `/review`
- DO NOT use `--dangerously-skip-permissions` outside a sandbox environment

## SDD flow
- Start with `/sdd-doctor check`
- Per feature: `/spec` → `/clarify` → `/plan` → `/tasks` → `/implement <id>` → `/review`
- Specifications live in `specs/<feature-slug>/`
- Capabilities (specialist agents + skills) are defined in `.claude/capabilities.md`
